        For years his practice has helped people transform limiting patterns into resourceful
        states — while his research pursues a larger question: <b>how meaning, emotion, and
        the sense of being are structured within the psyche.</b>
      </p>
      <p class="body" data-lang-en>
        Out of that inquiry grew <b>psychoontology</b> — his active line of development that
        treats the mind not only as something to be adjusted, but as a mode of <i>being</i>
        to be understood. This site gathers his books, articles, and lectures.
      </p>
